(raw mean difference) (: ) (measure) . \(\Delta\) .

\[ \Delta = \mu_1 - \mu_2 \] , \(\Delta\) (treatment and control) \(\bar{X}_1\) \(\bar{X}_2\) \(D\) .

\[ D = \bar{X}_1 - \bar{X}_2 \] , , \(\sigma_1 = \sigma_2 = \sigma\), \(i\) \(D_1\) .

\[ Var(D_i )=\frac{n_1 + n_2}{n_1 n_2}S_p^2 \] \(n_1\) , \(n_2\) , (pooled variance estimator) \(S_p^2\) \[ S_p^2 = \frac{(n_1-1)S_1^2 + (n_2-1)S_2^2}{n_1 +n_2 -2} \] , \(S_1^2\) \(S_2^2\) .

, , \(\sigma_1 \ne \sigma_2\), \(i\) \(S_i\) . \[ Var(D_i) = \frac{S_1^2}{n_1}+\frac{S_2^2}{n_2} \]

(standard error) \(S_p\) . \[ SE(D_i ) = \sqrt{Var(D_i)} \] \(i\) . \[ CI = D_i \pm z_{\alpha/2} \times SE(D_i ) \] \(i\) (inverse variance) . \[ w_i = \frac{1}{Var(D_i)} \]

\(M\) , . \[ M = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^K w_iD_i}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i} \] \(M\) . \[ Var(M)=\frac{1}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i}, \quad SE(M)=\sqrt{Var(M)} \]

. \[ CI=M\pm z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(M) \]

(standardized mean difference; SMD) Cohens \(d\) , \(i\) \(d_i\) .

\[ d_i = \frac{\bar{X_1}-\bar{X_2}}{S_p} \]

\(S_p\) (pooled standard deviation estimator) , \(S_p\) .

\[ S_p = \sqrt{\frac{(n_1 -1)S_1^2 + (n_2-1)S_2^2}{n_1+n_2-2}} \]

\(S_1^2\) \(S_2^2\) .

\(t\) \(F\) \(d_i\) .

  • \(t\) :

\[ d_i = t_i\sqrt{\frac{n_1+n_2}{n_1n_2}} \]

  • \(F\) :

\[ d_i = \sqrt{\frac{F_i (n_1+n_2)}{n_1n_2}} \]

\(d_i\) .

\[ Var(d_i)=\frac{1}{n_1}+\frac{1}{n_2}+\frac{d_i^2}{2(n_1+n_2)}=\frac{n_1+n_2}{n_1n_2}+\frac{d_i^2}{2(n_1+n_2)} \]

(2) (adjusted)

Cohens d (\(n \le 20\)) . (adjust) Hedgesg .

\[ g_i = J \times d, \,\,\, J=1-\frac{3}{4(n_1+n_2)-9} \] Hedges g .

\[ Var(g_i)=J^2\times Var(d_i) \]


(3)

.

  • Cohens d : \[ CI(d_i)=d_i \pm z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(d_i), \quad SE(d_i)=\sqrt{Var(d_i)} \]

  • Hedges g : \[ CI(g_i)=g_i \pm z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(g_i), \quad SE(g_i)=\sqrt{Var(g_i)} \]


(4)

. , (weight) (mean effect size) .

, .

\[ W_i = \frac{1}{Var_i} \]

, , .

  • Cohens d :

\[ M_d = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^K w_id_i}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i} \]

  • Hedges g :

\[ M_g = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^K w_ig_i}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i} \]


(5) (standard error of the mean)

, , .

  • : \[M = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^K w_ig_i}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i}\]

  • : \[V_M = \frac{1}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i}, \quad SE(M)=\sqrt{V_M}\]

  • (Test statistic) under \(H_0: M=0\) \[Z=\frac{M}{SE(M)}\]

  • : \[CI=(M-z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(M), M+z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(M))\]


(6) \(t\), \(F\) (\(p-value\))

  • \(t\): \[d=\pm t\sqrt{\frac{n_1+n_2}{n_1n_2}}\]

  • \(F\): \[d=\sqrt{\frac{F(n_1+n_2)}{n_1n_2}}\]

  • \(p-value\) : \[d=\pm t_{p-value}\sqrt{\frac{n_1+n_2}{n_1n_2}}\]

  • \(p<\alpha\) : \[d=\pm t_{\alpha}\sqrt{\frac{n_1+n_2}{n_1n_2}}\]

\(Log(RR)\) :

\[ Var(Log(RR_i))=\frac{1}{a}-\frac{1}{n_1}+\frac{1}{c}-\frac{1}{n_2} \] \(Log(RR)\) . \[ CI=Log(RR_i) \pm z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(Log(RR_i)) \] (RR) \(Log(RR)\) (exponential) . \[ CI(RR)=exp(Log(RR_i) \pm z_{\alpha/2}\times SE(Log(RR_i))) \] (Inverse variance) Mantel-Haenszel (MH) .

\(w\) \(Log(RR)\) . \[ w_i = \frac{1}{Var(Log(RR_i))} \] \(Log(\theta)\) . \[ Log(\theta)=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i Log(RR_i)}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i} \] \(Log(\theta)\) .

  • \(Log(\theta)\) \[ Var(Log(\theta)) = \frac{1}{\sum_{i=1}^K w_i} \]

Mantel-Haenszel (MH)

.

(\(r\)) (\(d\)) .

\[ d=\frac{2r}{\sqrt{1-r^2}} \] \[ Var(d)=\frac{4Var(r)}{(1-r^2)^3} \]

(\(d\)) (\(r\)) .

\[ r=\frac{d}{\sqrt{d^2+a}} \] , \(n_1 \ne n_2\) \(a\)

\[ a=\frac{(n_1+n_2)^2}{n_1n_2} \] , \(n_1\) \(n_2\) \(n_1=n_2\) \(a=4\)

\[ Var(r)=\frac{a^2Var(d)}{(d^2+a)^3} \]
